ococcus and Prochlorococcus (Cyanobacteria) (2007) J Phycol, 43, pp. 485-496; Geider, R.J., Osborne, R.A., (1992) Algal photosynthesis: The measurement of algal gas exchange, , Chapman & Hall, New York; Hare, C.E., DiTullio, G.R., Trick, C.G., Wilhelm, S.W., Bruland, K.W., Rue, E.L., Hutchins, D.A., Phytoplankton community structure changes following simulated upwelled iron inputs in the Peru upwelling region (2005) Aquat Microb Ecol, 38, pp. 269-282; Hare, C.E., DiTullio, G.R., Popels, L.C., Riseman, S.F., Crossley, A.C., Sedwick, P.N., Hutchins, D.A., Effects of changing continuous iron input rates on a Southern Ocean algal assemblage (2007) Deep-Sea Res I, 54, pp. 732-746; Hare, S.R., Mantura, N.J., Empirical evidence for North Pacific regime shifts in 1977 and 1989 (2000) Prog Oceanogr, 47, pp. 103-146; Hays, G.C., Richardson, A.J., Robinson, C., Climate change and marine plankton (2005) Trends Ecol Evol, 20, pp. 337-344; Hutchins, D.A., Pustizzi, F., Hare, C.E., DiTullio, G.R., A shipboard natural community continuous culture system for ecologically relevant low-level nutrient enrichment experiments (2003) Limnol Oceanogr Methods, 1, pp. 82-91; Hutchins, D.A., Fu, F.X., Zhang, Y., Warner, M.E., Feng, Y., Portune, K., Bernhardt, P.W., Mulholland, M.R., CO2 control of Trichodesmium N 2 fixation, photosynthesis, growth rates, and elemental ratios: Implications for past, present, and future ocean biogeochemistry (2007) Limnol Oceanogr, 52, pp. 1293-1304; Climate change 2001: The Scientific Basis. In: Houghton JT, Ding Y, Griggs DJ, Noguer M, van der Linden PJ (2001) Xiaosu D (eds) Contributions of the Working Group I to the Third Assessment Report of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change, pp. 1-786. , IPCC Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change, Cambridge University Press, Cambridge, p; Kim, J.M., Lee, K., Shin, K., Kang, J.H., Lee, H.W., Kim, M., Jang, P.G., Jang, M.C., The effects of seawater CO2 concentration on growth of a natural phytoplankton assem